  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study, a randomized controlled study was conducted between two groups of 20 classic
      recipients of intradermal sutures and 20 recipients of intradermal staple methods for
      patients undergoing the same cervical incision. This is a study to see if there is any
      difference in pain and esthetics in scar formation of these groups.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
